name: Mechanical Squirrel
description: A mechanical squirrel's logic center tells it to collect and store both nuts and bolts for the winter.

name: Bombay Cat
description: Donni Anthania plans to have a bombay buried with her when she dies. A wise adventurer can put its talents to much better use.

name: Cornish Rex Cat
description: Donni Anthania invites these cats to her tea parties. But she doesn't serve their favorite drink: the tears of their enemies.

name: Black Tabby Cat
description: Old Alterac saying: 'A cat has nine lives, but needs only one.'

name: Orange Tabby Cat
description: The last person who tried to housebreak this cat quickly learned that a soiled rug is better than a shredded everything-else.

name: Siamese Cat
description: Known for its blue eyes. Also considered a delicacy by giant murlocs.

name: Silver Tabby Cat
description: Sleeping is this cat's second favorite activity. The first is yawning.

name: White Kitten
description: The queen had three kittens. The first gave her a juicy rat. The second, a tasty hare. And the white, her favorite, presented the head of her rival.

name: Cockatiel
description: Some say this clever bird can be taught to speak--but it's smart enough to keep its beak shut.

name: Hyacinth Macaw
description: The jungle trolls train these birds to mimic calls for help in order to lure unsuspecting travelers into traps.

name: Green Wing Macaw
description: Favored pet of the Defias pirates, this colorful bird is handy for remembering passwords, grocery lists, and cracker recipes.

name: Senegal
description: Favored pet of the goblins of Booty Bay, this colorful bird is renowned for its ability to count coins, tally budgets, and lie about contracts.

name: Ancona Chicken
description: It thinks you taste like chicken too.

name: Undercity Cockroach
description: The cockroach is usually an impulse buy. Its owners have a hard time parting with it even after numerous attempts.

name: Dark Whelpling
description: Hopes that someday it can grow up to destroy villages, just like mommy.

name: Azure Whelpling
description: Like other members of the blue dragonflight, these whimsical little critters display an affinity to arcane magic.

name: Crimson Whelpling
description: Hailing from the Wetlands, this young dragon is just learning how to hunt, breathe fire, and go on cute destructive rampages.

name: Emerald Whelpling
description: Once bred and raised by the green dragon Itharius, this unique breed of dragon has settled in the jungles of Feralas.

name: Wood Frog
description: Vendors at the Darkmoon Faire offer strange and exotic wonders. They also sell wood frogs.

name: Tree Frog
description: Known for their powerful legs and keen eyesight.

name: Hawk Owl
description: This dark-feathered bird of prey is often seen as a harbinger of doom amongst the druids of Teldrassil.

name: Great Horned Owl
description: Night elf children are given an owl feather on their first birthday as a token of good luck.

name: Snowy Owl
description: Winterspring's furbolg prize the brilliant white feathers of these majestic creatures for ritual purposes.

name: Brown Prairie Dog
description: A complex system of burrows protects the prairie dog from its neighbors' massive hooves.

name: Snowshoe Rabbit
description: If you go chasing snowshoe rabbits, you know you're going to fall.

name: Albino Snake
description: A favored companion of Kirin Tor magi, this reptile makes one wonder whether it's truly a snake or something else altogether.

name: Black Kingsnake
description: Xan'tish fearlessly tracks, captures, and trains these noble snakes so they will aid their comrades in battle.

name: Brown Snake
description: The brown snake is native to Horde-controlled territories. It seems unremarkable until its victims are within range.

name: Crimson Snake
description: The crimson snake is favored among the Darkspear trolls for not only its vicious nature, but also its steadfast loyalty.

name: Mechanical Chicken
description: Not to worry; the combat mechanisms and homing logic have been disabled on this unit, I think. --Oglethorpe Obnoticus

name: Westfall Chicken
description: Don't call this bird chicken unless you want egg on your face.

name: Pet Bombling
description: Possibly explosive, definitely adorable. Keep away from open flame.

name: Lil' Smoky
description: This tiny peacekeeper security bot is often outfitted with the latest arcane nullifiers and crowd pummelers. Not for the environmentally minded.

name: Sprite Darter Hatchling
description: These adorable critters love snuggling with their owners after a long day of brutal, bloody battle.

name: Worg Pup
description: Worgs are the favored companions of orcs and are fiercely loyal on the battlefield.

name: Smolderweb Hatchling
description: Although born in the warm heights of Blackrock Spire, the smolderweb hatchling can survive most environments.

name: Panda Cub
description: This pint-sized panda cub is highly sought after by adventurers around Azeroth - despite its narcoleptic nature.

name: Mini Diablo
description: AND THE HEAVENS SHALL TREMBLE, AND MAN SHALL WEEP, AND THE END OF DAYS SHALL--wait, why are you so tall?

name: Zergling
description: A small, fierce member of the Zerg swarm, the zergling is not to be trifled with. Very dangerous in high numbers.

name: Lifelike Toad
description: Talented engineers have crafted an exact replica of a wood frog, at only ten times the cost of buying the real thing.

name: Jubling
description: The legendary ale frog was believed to be extinct until the strange brews at the Darkmoon Faire brought them out of hiding.

name: Murky
description: Appearances of this beloved and ultra-reclusive murloc are sure to draw a crowd.

name: Lurky
description: Lurky's charming disposition and lively antics are guaranteed to soothe frustration and lighten even the darkest moods.

name: Disgusting Oozeling
description: Warning: Wear gloves and goggles while handling disgusting oozeling. DO NOT WASH. Will stain most armor.

name: Land Shark
description: After birth, newborn sharks quickly flee their hungry mothers. Their early independence makes them dangerous, even while young.

name: Tranquil Mechanical Yeti
description: This clever toy is equipped with a secret switch to disable its 'tranquil' mode. Luckily, even the engineers who built it don't know how to find it.

name: Tiny Snowman
description: He loves to dance and wave and play with you! He melts after Winter Veil, but don't worry; he'll be back again someday!

name: Winter Reindeer
description: Would rather not spend any more time inside a wrapped holiday gift box.

name: Father Winter's Helper
description: These off-season allies work tirelessly to prepare for the Feast of Winter Veil, and would appreciate not being disturbed the rest of the year.

name: Winter's Little Helper
description: During the majestic Winter Veil celebration, these faithful companions spread joy throughout the land. The rest of the year, they are busy.

name: Gurky
description: Gurky is a born performer, though she remains elusive, making public appearances only on the rarest of occasions.

name: Peddlefeet
description: The power of love can be a dangerous thing, especially when wielded by an airborne, ill-tempered goblin.

name: Poley
description: This cub shares many traits with its relatives, but it's in a league of its own with its singing ability.

name: Speedy
description: Slow and steady wins the race.

name: Mr. Wiggles
description: Many assume 'Wiggles' refers to the motion of this pig's posterior. They discover the true meaning when they see their own entrails.

name: Whiskers the Rat
description: A clever tactician, Whiskers will feign death to fool predators and bill collectors.

name: Spirit of Summer
description: This little piece of summer smells of warm evenings and lightning storms. If you look closely, you might be able to make out a face.

name: Hippogryph Hatchling
description: After a harpy incursion in Feralas, several hippogryph nesting grounds were attacked. Hundreds of hatchlings were orphaned, and they have been entrusted to the care of the druids on Sardor Isle.

name: Netherwhelp
description: Offspring of the nether drakes of Outland, this young dragon is still growing into its role as hunter, protector, and adorable terror of the skies.

name: Magical Crawdad
description: Only magical wishes make magical crawdads. If you wish for a fish, fish for a wish.

name: Mana Wyrmling
description: The ethereal Rashaad began breeding these enigmatic creatures after learning of their ability to feed on arcane energies.

name: Brown Rabbit
description: This bunny is the cutest thing its opponent will ever see. It'll also be the last.

name: Blue Moth
description: Delicate denizen of Azuremyst Isle, this magical insect has been rumored to possess healing abilities.

name: Red Moth
description: A product of exposure to wild magical energies, this insect is the unexpectedly colorful result of Azerothian moth species being released into the eco-domes of the Netherstorm.

name: Yellow Moth
description: Prefers flying during thunderstorms, which are common in Azuremyst Isle.

name: White Moth
description: Prefers flying during foggy nights, which are common in Azuremyst Isle.

name: Golden Dragonhawk Hatchling
description: Once prized by dragonhawk breeders in Silvermoon. Stands out at night to predators, making it necessary to gain awareness at an early age.

name: Red Dragonhawk Hatchling
description: Mortal enemies with silver dragonhawks; on pretty good terms with golden dragonhawks.

name: Silver Dragonhawk Hatchling
description: Ferocious species of dragonhawk, often seen diving down on prey from high in the sky.

name: Blue Dragonhawk Hatchling
description: Raised by the few dealers still willing to trade in Netherstorm.

name: Firefly
description: Commonly used by sporelings as a light source as they navigate the waterways of Zangarmarsh, this luminescent insect helps them avoid the dangerous bogflare needlers.

name: Miniwing
description: The magical energies released during Skywing's transformation back into his true arakkoa form liberated this poor creature, a fledgling bird imprisoned by Luanga in order to power his fowl curse.

name: Wolpertinger
description: Many a drunken Brewfest goer has told the tale of this mysterious creature, but few remember that tale in the morning.

name: Lucky
description: Lucky squeals when he's angry or when he's eating. Either way, you don't want to bother him.

name: Bananas
description: Although loath to part with Bananas, Landro realized it would be safer if the pet was far from Booty Bay when his father, King Mukla, discovered he was missing.

name: Willy
description: He's slightly evil but extremely narcoleptic. Keep him away from critters!

name: Egbert
description: The sin'dorei use hawkstriders as mounts, but this little one was deemed unfit after being diagnosed with numerous anxiety disorders.

name: Peanut
description: Domesticated elekks are trained as mounts by the draenei people. In the wild they are hunted for their ivory tusks.

name: Stinker
description: Stinker uses his aroma to repel predators and attract cats. He's much more successful with the former than the latter.

name: Sinister Squashling
description: This mischievous gourd likes to pop out of the ground and scare you right out of your pants. Hail to the pumpkin song!

name: Toothy
description: The crocolisk's hide and meat are prized by hunters, but the beast is ferocious and seldom taken by surprise.

name: Muckbreath
description: Muckbreath is just like other crocolisks, except he has an excellent sense of humor.

name: Mojo
description: Amani witch doctors have turned many victims into frogs. Some never recover.

name: Pint-Sized Pink Pachyderm
description: A shy creature, the pink elekk will only make its presence known to those that have befriended it, or to anyone too intoxicated to harm it.

name: Tiny Sporebat
description: Wild sporebats are vicious creatures, but if tamed at a young age, they can be loyal companions.

name: Rocket Chicken
description: When the Burning Legion invaded Outland, Landro Longshot contributed this design to the war effort. Both the Alliance and Horde passed on production.

name: Dragon Kite
description: Much quieter than a real dragon.

name: Golden Pig
description: This golden pig honors its ancestors by giving its allies good fortune.

name: Silver Pig
description: Druids think silver pigs have a special bond with golden pigs, as both breeds appeared on Azeroth at the same time.

name: Searing Scorchling
description: Elder shaman have warned that wisps of Ragnaros, loyal servants of the Firelord, have taken to the Molten Front. Vigilance is advised.

name: Snarly
description: Crocolisks are six-legged amphibian predators found in coastal waters. Archaeologists believe they may be descended from the diemetradons of Un'Goro Crater.

name: Chuck
description: After studying the crocolisk species for several years, the famed angler Nat Pagle determined that baby crocolisks are mostly harmless.

name: Phoenix Hatchling
description: A child of phoenix god Al'ar, the hatchling takes flight immediately after birth.

name: Spirit of Competition
description: These stunning creatures, awarded to heroes for victory in battle, represent bravery and strength.

name: Essence of Competition
description: Only heroes who have proven their valor through great acts are gifted one of these mystical serpentine creatures.

name: Ethereal Soul-Trader
description: Ethereal soul-traders will travel with those who can free the essences they need from unruly hosts.

name: Nether Ray Fry
description: Native to the Terokkar Forest, nether rays spawn during the rainy season. Out of the hundreds of offspring resulting from one hatching, very few survive to adulthood.

name: Vampiric Batling
description: Vampire bats have been trained as scouts and mounts by the Forsaken of the Undercity and the Amani trolls of Zul'Aman.

name: Frosty
description: Accidentally created when the Lich King's deathly powers raised Rimefang from undeath.

name: Mini Tyrael
description: 'I am Justice itself!'

name: Ghostly Skull
description: When it senses the impending death of a nearby creature, the skull will emit an ear-piercing cackle.

name: Clockwork Rocket Bot
description: This mechanical warrior is a favorite gift during Winter Veil. Batteries not included, but rockets definitely are!

name: Mr. Chilly
description: Mr. Chilly's appearance evokes a more civilized era, when duelists battled in tuxedos.

name: Giant Sewer Rat
description: You wouldn't want to meet this rat in a dark alley. Or anywhere else, for that matter.

name: Tickbird Hatchling
description: Unlike most of Geen the gorloc's 'mysterious eggs,' this one actually contained a living thing.

name: White Tickbird Hatchling
description: The rare albino tickbird is revered amongst the Oracles. It is seen as a sign of heavy rainstorms, good grub harvests, and hibernating wolvar.

name: Proto-Drake Whelp
description: These voracious whelps grow at an incredible rate and can devour nearly twice their weight in raw meat per day.

name: Cobra Hatchling
description: The cobras of Azeroth are renowned for their fast-acting venom and swift strikes.

name: Pengu
description: Notable for its wide eyes and sassy slide.

name: Kirin Tor Familiar
description: To prevent apprentices from secretly using the familiar to complete their chores, the archmagi placed the ritual required to summon the creature across the pages of several spellbooks hidden throughout Dalaran.

name: Spring Rabbit
description: Spring rabbits symbolize fertility, and they love to demonstrate why.

name: Plump Turkey
description: He's humble, clairvoyant, and delicious with cranberry sauce.

name: Baby Blizzard Bear
description: This rare bear is bred for its small size and perpetually youthful appearance.

name: Little Fawn
description: She likes the company of friends. Seventy-five of them, to be precise.

name: Teldrassil Sproutling
description: It always wakes up dancing. What a happy little tree!

name: Dun Morogh Cub
description: The bears of Dun Morogh are prized for their hardiness, loyalty, and combat prowess. Their time among the dwarves does little to curb their ferocity.

name: Tirisfal Batling
description: Can sense an opponent's heartbeat through echolocation.

name: Durotar Scorpion
description: The volatile Durotar scorpion is a fierce desert predator. It's known for only occasionally stinging its owner.

name: Elwynn Lamb
description: Unlike the polymorphed variety, trueborn sheep can be quite scary.

name: Mulgore Hatchling
description: A tallstrider's speed on open ground is unrivaled, so predators rely on stealth and pack tactics when hunting them.

name: Strand Crawler
description: The strand crawler has adapted to the northern cold by hibernating under the island beaches.

name: Ammen Vale Lashling
description: The long-term effects of the contamination caused by the Exodar are still under observation.

name: Enchanted Broom
description: Created by a blood elf apprentice, this broom would be extremely useful if anyone could figure out how to make it stop.

name: Argent Squire
description: Many of Stormwind's youth joined the Argent Crusade as squires, hoping to one day serve the Holy Light in battle.

name: Mechanopeep
description: Used as a training mount for young gnomes, the Mechanopeep has none of the speed but all of the charm of its bigger brothers.

name: Argent Gruntling
description: These young orcs strive to embody the Argent Crusade's virtues: valor, strength, and integrity.

name: Murkimus the Gladiator
description: Murkimus is the most fearsome of all murloc arena warriors. And for a time, the only one.

name: Sen'jin Fetish
description: This is actually three pets in one. You won't know what you'll get until you summon it!

name: Withers
description: A solemn reminder of what was lost when the Worldbreaker changed the face of Azeroth.

name: Calico Cat
description: Many have mocked this cat before battle. Their last words are usually, 'Here, kitty, kitty.'

name: Curious Oracle Hatchling
description: The bouncy gurloc is a distant cousin of the murloc.

name: Curious Wolvar Pup
description: Despite their smaller stature, the wolvar are some of the most aggressive creatures in Northrend. This often makes their curious nature intimidating.

name: Warbot
description: A fighting robot fueled by delicious red or blue electrolytes.

name: Grunty
description: Only the rarest of murlocs is able to successfully cross dimensional barriers. Fewer still return with the kind of advanced armor and weaponry possessed by Grunty.

name: Shimmering Wyrmling
description: This extremely rare species of mana wyrm is prized for its unique coloration and even temperament.

name: Jade Tiger
description: Considered to be lucky, tigers carved of jade are prized, but taming a jade tiger itself is an even greater prize.

name: Darting Hatchling
description: Rarely leaves nest until maturity. Enjoys conducting pranks on the nearby Razormaw nest.

name: Deviate Hatchling
description: The demand for this purple-skinned breed has drastically reduced the raptor population near the Wailing Caverns.

name: Gundrak Hatchling
description: This crafty raptor was born in the icy wastes of Northrend. Its harsh upbringing gives it strength when many others would perish.

name: Leaping Hatchling
description: This offspring of Takk the Leaper is incredibly agile and can maneuver through difficult environments with ease.

name: Obsidian Hatchling
description: This hatchling is coveted for its unique coloration. Despite Breanni's loving care, the raptor's feral nature cannot be restrained.

name: Ravasaur Hatchling
description: Larger than other raptor infants, these hatchlings grow into towering reptilian beasts capable of massive devastation.

name: Razormaw Hatchling
description: Razormaw eggs are protected fiercely by their mothers. Their cuteness belies their inherited ferocity.

name: Razzashi Hatchling
description: Razzashi raptors are among the cleverest predators in the jungle, making them favored by the Gurubashi trolls.

name: Onyx Panther
description: The onyx panther is invisible at night, like a stalking shadow, and disappears with the dawn.

name: Tuskarr Kite
description: Seeing these kites soaring above Northrend's shores is a clear sign that tuskarr are nearby.

name: Spectral Tiger Cub
description: Affectionate and curious, these kittens seem to find the most peculiar hiding places.

name: Onyxian Whelpling
description: Spawn of Onyxia, this young dragon has decided that it doesn't want to follow in its grandfathers' cataclysmic footsteps.

name: Core Hound Pup
description: Found in the Firelands and the Molten Core, core hounds can trace their lineage back to the alpha male, Magmadar.

name: Gryphon Hatchling
description: A gift from the Wildhammer dwarves to the heroes of the Alliance, these hatchlings are descendants of the same gryphons ridden by Falstad and his entourage into Grim Batol.

name: Wind Rider Cub
description: Thorg No-Legs never paid heed to the old orc saying, 'Don't pull a wyvern's tail.'

name: Zipao Tiger
description: A rarely seen family of tigers, many believe (perhaps incorrectly) that some residual magic or other event is responsible for the unique color.

name: Pandaren Monk
description: The pandaren monk is a fearless traveling companion, constantly training in his art... unless you offer him a drink. He considers it rude to refuse.

name: Lil' K.T.
description: In life, Kel'Thuzad betrayed the Kirin Tor and created the Cult of the Damned. In death, he serves the Scourge as the Archlich Lord of Naxxramas.

name: Perky Pug
description: Although small, pugs are very dangerous when provoked.

name: Toxic Wasteling
description: This, um, 'adorable' little guy likes to play with critters. Just don't let them get too close.

name: Frigid Frostling
description: While not nearly as destructive as its original master, the Ice Lord Ahune, the frostling has been known to lob chilly snowballs at unsuspecting adventurers.

name: Blue Clockwork Rocket Bot
description: Jepetto's top-selling toy this season, the bot's new blue chassis has children across Azeroth scrambling for this feisty battle bot.

name: Celestial Dragon
description: Breanni in Dalaran, one of the world's foremost collectors of exotic pets, will only award the mystical Celestial Dragon to fellow collectors whose obsession rivals her own.

name: Lil' XT
description: Modeled after the huge titan prototype in Ulduar, this volatile little construct plays hard with its toys.

name: Mini Thor
description: Powerful artillery of the Terran army. The Thor is always the first one in and the last one out!

name: Blue Mini Jouster
description: Unlike its gold counterpart, the blue mini jouster takes a leisurely pace when jabbing its opponent's eyeballs.

name: Gold Mini Jouster
description: This critter is infamous for its ability to unleash a fast and furious eyeball jabbing.

name: Personal World Destroyer
description: Goblin engineering at its finest. Blueprints based on the massive fel reaver in Hellfire Peninsula.

name: De-Weaponized Mechanical Companion
description: The gold standard for sturdy gnomish design, this mechanical critter is the perfect companion for the lonely engineer on the go.

name: Crawling Claw
description: This appears to be nothing more than the paw of a small primate. A closer inspection shows that the hand has been dried by centuries of exposure to the sands of Uldum.

name: Pebble
description: An adventurous little elemental, Pebble escaped hungry gyreworms in the Crumbling Depths, braved the emptiness of the Twisting Nether, and ultimately found himself rescued from a mailbox.

name: Fossilized Hatchling
description: You stare at her, and she just stares right back. So clever; sometimes it seems as if she's figuring out how to open doors.

name: Enchanted Lantern
description: Reduces the likelihood of being eaten by monsters when you enter pitch-black places.

name: Lil' Deathwing
description: Nations tremble under his shadow - the Destroyer, the one-time Aspect of Earth, and the monster responsible for breaking Azeroth asunder. Now in a convenient travel-size!

name: Dark Phoenix Hatchling
description: Fire hatchlings are born from the ashes of a phoenix. Dark hatchlings emerge from their shadows.

name: Rustberg Gull
description: This bird is a salty veteran of the endless naval battles surrounding Tol Barad--a veteran whose grown plump from picking through the leftovers, that is.

name: Armadillo Pup
description: Rolls into a protective ball when it feels threatened. Or when its mother calls.

name: Clockwork Gnome
description: Thought to be an original construct of the titans, the clockwork gnome has some gears smaller than the eye can see.

name: Fox Kit
description: The fighting in Tol Barad has made it difficult to find these kits, and numerous would-be owners have decimated the fox population there as a result.

name: Tiny Shale Spider
description: The elemental shale spider is no true arachnid, but it has durability and ferocity that make it feared even in Deepholm.

name: Guild Page
description: Guild pages must be fearless since they are called upon to announce their guild's victories over the Horde in battle.

name: Guild Page
description: When a guild earns enough glory by defeating Alliance champions, some orcs will come to share the glory by serving the guild.

name: Guild Herald
description: When guilds have accumulated enough wealth, brave soldiers are often called to bear their standards.

name: Guild Herald
description: Wealthy guilds draw the attention of soldiers willing to carry their standards into battle.

name: Landro's Lil' XT
description: Always 'ready to play,' Landro's Lil' XT is almost indistinguishable from the original. Prone to tantrums and narcolepsy.

name: Mr. Grubbs
description: The grubs of the Plaguelands are a side effect of necromantic corruption and the massive number of corpses there. Mr. Grubbs is from a particularly acrobatic breed.

name: Tiny Flamefly
description: After swarming around open lava pits during the day, these strange insects emit a fiery glow at night.

name: Scooter the Snail
description: You'll find him in his shell, exactly where a snail has to be!

name: Singing Sunflower
description: This sweet flower will brighten your day with its warm smile and cheerful song! Also strong against undead.

name: Magic Lamp
description: Higitus figi- hockity pocki- abracadab- prestidig--oh, pinfeathers!

name: Elementium Geode
description: Often confused by miners as a rare gem, the geode initially makes its presence known by emitting melodic reverberations.

name: Deathy
description: Deathwing's emergence transformed the whole of Azeroth; not even the ocean-dwelling murlocs were immune to his corrupt influence.

name: Moonkin Hatchling
description: Moonkin are blessed by Elune and spread nature's grace wherever they travel. The festive fowls are always in the mood for a dance.

name: Lil' Ragnaros
description: It's never too soon to summon this tiny aspect of the dread Firelord.

name: Moonkin Hatchling
description: The distinct roar of the moonkin is one of the most terrifying sounds in nature.

name: Panther Cub
description: It looked up at you with those huge black eyes and seemed to ask, 'Are you my mommy?'

name: Landro's Lichling
description: How the goblin Landro Longshot initially came into possession of the lichling remains a mystery, but he was all too eager to wager it in a game of cards.

name: Nightsaber Cub
description: Elune made nightsabers silver and black so they could meld into the shadows on a moonlit night.

name: Winterspring Cub
description: Winterspring cubs are happiest when frolicking in freshly fallen snow.

name: Lashtail Hatchling
description: Born in the jungles of Stranglethorn, unlucky raptor hatchlings are often captured by the Gurubashi and taken to the troll city of Zul'Gurub.

name: Legs
description: Wild marsh walkers are dangerously aggressive, but they're loyal and affectionate if you manage to tame them.

name: Pterrordax Hatchling
description: Pterrordax eggs are incubated underneath the fossils of their forebears, allowing the hatchlings to absorb their ancestors' ferocity and intelligence.

name: Voodoo Figurine
description: Voodoo figurines were often empowered by flasks of mojo, troll sweat, and the flesh of tribal enemies.

name: Guardian Cub
description: Still a little clumsy, this tiny winged lion is learning how to be the best mount it can be!

name: Cenarion Hatchling
description: Not yet the fearsome creatures they grow to in adulthood, the Cenarion hatchlings have an almost harmless appearance that has caught novice trainers of the Cenarion Circle off guard.

name: Hyjal Bear Cub
description: The cubs of Hyjal suffered much during the Cataclysm. On the bright side, the devastation also led to their newfound love of heights and daredevil stunts.

name: Crimson Lasher
description: Native to the ashen soils of the Firelands, the lasher was transplanted to Azeroth with the help of the Guardians of Hyjal.

name: Feline Familiar
description: Ride with the moon (and this furry, whiskered witch) in the dead of night!

name: Lil' Tarecgosa
description: A legendary member of the blue dragonflight.

name: Creepy Crate
description: Previous owners of the crate have reported the disappearance of other pets from their collection.

name: Nuts
description: Most squirrels hoard acorns for sustenance. Nuts, on the other hand, hoards acorns to stock its supply of ammunition.

name: Brilliant Kaliri
description: One of the rarest creatures, this kaliri is set apart from others by its brilliant plumage and the lengths hunters will go to capture them.

name: Purple Puffer
description: You might think this fish out of water would be a weak opponent... until you see the intensity that lies within its protective bubble.

name: Murkablo
description: When you're confronting Murkablo or any of the Prime Murlocs, possession of a soulstone is strongly advised.

name: Darkmoon Monkey
description: The monkeys of Azeroth are infamous tricksters, and these beloved companions of the Darkmoon Faire have taken that innate cunning to a whole new level.

name: Alliance Balloon
description: Created to entertain children at the Darkmoon Faire, these magical balloons never lose their floatiness.

name: Horde Balloon
description: A magical wonder, these balloons will never deflate and are traditionally created in batches of ninety-nine.

name: Gregarious Grell
description: The grell are embodiments of the wild side of nature. Tame ones are very rare.

name: Darkmoon Turtle
description: This shelled reptile bravely protects the home on its back with an unwaveringly happy disposition.

name: Darkmoon Balloon
description: It just floats along...

name: Lumpy
description: A stowaway from Greatfather Winter's workshop, this tiny elemental found himself trapped in a present that was stolen by the Abominable Greench.

name: Darkmoon Tonk
description: A favorite of children across Azeroth, this tough little toy can withstand even the most aggressive imagination.

name: Darkmoon Zeppelin
description: Lacking the mines and rockets of its predecessor, this kid-friendly faire prize is a new favorite among Azeroth's children.

name: Sea Pony
description: Despite its diminutive size, it is impossible to miss a sea pony cutting through the water.

name: Lunar Lantern
description: These magical lanterns are acquired at the Lunar Festival, which celebrates the defeat of the Burning Legion by the free races of Azeroth.

name: Festival Lantern
description: The light from each lantern honors the soul of an ancestor spirit. During the Lunar Festival, these ghostly elders pass along their wisdom to the current generation.

name: Darkmoon Cub
description: This snuggly kitten loves to frolic, but sometimes it seems to be chasing things that aren't really there.

name: Fetish Shaman
description: Fetish shaman are empowered by the spirits of their fallen ancestors. These malevolent spirits are bound to the shaman's tribal spear. Control this spear, and you control the shaman.

name: Soul of the Aspects
description: The Soul of the Aspects is said to be possessed of mercurial moods ranging from stoic and deliberate to unpredictable and erratic, to loving and deeply pensive.

name: Eye of the Legion
description: Always watching. Always judging.

name: Black Lamb
description: Offspring of the black sheep, the black lamb is only found in the forests of Elwynn.

name: Rabbit
description: When you have two rabbits, you'll often soon have three.

name: Squirrel
description: Most people do not know the difference between a squirrel and a chipmunk. Most don't care.

name: Bucktooth Flapper
description: It's hard to know what's more dangerous: the teeth or the tail.

name: Porcupette
description: Despite the name you should absolutely never, ever pet it.

name: Sun Darter Hatchling
description: This unique species of faerie dragon is not usually found on Azeroth.

name: Eternal Strider
description: It seems like a trick to the eyes, but the eternal strider can walk across water, its small feet never breaking the surface.

name: Mouse
description: It seems that mice are completely incapable of resisting cheese even in the face of imprisonment, injury, or death.

name: Prairie Dog
description: Distinct from their tree dwelling cousins, these ground squirrels make their homes on the plains of Azeroth and beyond.

name: Snake
description: Due to recent accidents, the goblin cartels have prohibited anyone from bringing snakes on a zeppelin.

name: Shore Crab
description: These arthropods line many Azerothian shores and seek to fulfill their one true desire: to pinch.

name: Tiny Harvester
description: The tiny harvester collects weeds and small grains that the larger reapers may have missed.

name: Mountain Cottontail
description: Mountain cottontails can leap up a steep incline with speed you would not believe.

name: Redridge Rat
description: The rats in Redridge grow fat from feasting on the bounty of the village larders.

name: Cockroach
description: They were here long before us and will be here long after we are gone.

name: Fledgling Buzzard
description: Always wear a helm in the Redridge Mountains. Buzzards view humanoid hair as excellent nesting material.

name: Dusk Spiderling
description: Native to Duskwood, these eight-legged critters are often used as ingredients in alchemy potions.

name: Skunk
description: Skunks are known as solitary creatures for reasons which are hopefully obvious.

name: Black Rat
description: While many people believe black cats to be bad luck, black rats are held in higher esteem.

name: Rat Snake
description: Years ago, humans introduced these reptiles into Duskwood to cull the local rat population.

name: Widow Spiderling
description: Widow spiderlings have plenty of time to explore Duskwood once they take care of their pesky family commitments.

name: Strand Crab
description: The low tide reveals the colonies of strand crabs and the sound of their clicking dance as they feed upon small creatures hidden in the sand.

name: Swamp Moth
description: Prefers to dwell in wet, muddy areas and feed on Sorrowmoss nectar.

name: Parrot
description: Parrots can mimic speech, but have difficulty with meaningful conversation.

name: Long-tailed Mole
description: Thought by many to be nothing more than the subject of children's nursery rhymes, the long-tailed mole is very much real.

name: Tree Python
description: Stranglethorn's Gurubashi trolls often capture these powerful beasts to keep as pets... or to cook as meals.

name: Beetle
description: A hardy insect that can dwell in just about any climate, the beetle is known to thrive on battlefields after the fighting has ended.

name: Forest Spiderling
description: This vicious species weaves elaborate webs throughout the dense jungles of Stranglethorn Vale.

name: Lizard Hatchling
description: If a female lizard does not lay her clutch in a well camouflaged area, her eggs will likely be devoured by Lashtail Raptors.

name: Alpine Hare
description: The alpine hare can burrow into the permafrost and hibernate for weeks or even months.

name: Blighthawk
description: Curiously, this hawk uses its razor-sharp talons to peel the bark off trees as it searches for bugs, even though it has no need for sustenance.

name: Silithid Hatchling
description: These hatchlings entertain themselves by clacking their mandibles together in increasingly complex rhythms.

name: Qiraji Guardling
description: The squeaks used by these tiny insectoids may sound cute, but they're actually screaming for your death.

name: Flayer Youngling
description: A brash fel orc once tried to enslave these critters as his personal soldiers. Pieces of him are still scattered across Outland.

name: Fel Flame
description: Born from demonic magic, these petulant little entities corrupt everything they touch with foul energies.

name: Scourged Whelpling
description: Kel'Thuzad once nursed a plague-infected whelp to adulthood, feeding it only the finest liquefied remains.

name: Nether Faerie Dragon
description: Much like other faerie dragons, these playful and mystical flyers are born with a natural defense against magic.

name: Arctic Hare
description: The heart of an arctic hare beats twice as fast as a common hare.

name: Micronax
description: Whenever his forces would experience setbacks in Azeroth, Kil'jaeden would pull out Micronax and terrorize the local cat-like creatures of Argus to vent his frustrations.

name: Alpine Foxling
description: Burrows deep into snowbanks to hide from predators.

name: Mongoose
description: Contrary to its benign appearance, mongoose are dangerous carnivores, well known for their ability to hunt venomous snakes that could kill much larger creatures.

name: Emperor Crab
description: The emperor crab was named for its regal appearance: the ridges of its shell and its raised claws eerily resembling a crown. One that would pinch your eyes out if you tried to wear it.

name: Mechanical Pandaren Dragonling
description: Constructed from a seemingly impossible mass of gears, springs, wires, and a little something special, this dragonling embodies the spirit of Pandaria as seen through an engineer's goggles.

name: Darkmoon Rabbit
description: This rabbit is much stronger than it looks.

name: Terky
description: Terky is as shy as she is adorable, preferring the company of close friends over new ones.

name: Mr. Bigglesworth
description: Upon exiting the freezing necropolis of Naxxramas, Mr. Bigglesworth promptly found a warm spot in the sun to take a long nap in.

name: Untamed Hatchling
description: One of Razorgore's eggs that miraculously survived in Blackwing Lair.

name: Chrominius
description: Opponents that face this fierce chromatic monstrosity just hope it doesn't have Time Stop!

name: Death Talon Whelpguard
description: A runt of the Black Talon, left to guard the whelps.

name: Nexus Whelpling
description: The runts of Malygos brood, these whelplings are prized for their boundless arcane magics.

name: Kun-Lai Runt
description: Indigenous to the peaks of Kun-Lai Summit, this rare yeti is much more dangerous than it looks.

name: Sunreaver Micro-Sentry
description: Loyal to the Sunreavers from creation, these pint-sized constructs can still pack a punch.

name: Son of Animus
description: Forged in the Throne of Thunder, these tiny creations are servants of the great Dark Animus.

name: Pygmy Direhorn
description: Don't pet the pointy end. Note: all of the ends are pointy.

name: Pierre
description: Every cook's dream wrapped up in a perfect bundle of metal and bolts. Too bad what he cooks up isn't suitable for humanoid consumption. According to Jard's notes, he intends to make this little guy for his friend, Emily Cole.

name: Direhorn Runt
description: The Zandalari breed specific Direhorn species for their small size for use as mounts.

name: Tiny Blue Carp
description: These little guys can be found in the waters of the Timeless Isle, or swimming alongside Jewel Danio or Redbelly Mandarin. Dedicated fishermen can sometimes befriend one.

name: Zandalari Anklerender
description: These tiny minions of Zandalar are adept at stowing away within the cargo holds of the enormous Zandalari warships.

name: Zandalari Toenibbler
description: These adorable beasts are both cuddly and huggable, provided you do not enjoy having a face.

name: Fiendish Imp
description: A minion of Terestian Illhoof, this tricky imp was left in Karazhan when the portal to the Twisting Nether closed behind it.

name: Unborn Val'kyr
description: Val'kyr are considered "unborn" until they vanquish a creature of high nobility.

name: Blossoming Ancient
description: This budding ancient is a unique variety in Azeroth, created from the ever-living branches of the Great Tree, and can bloom in any season.

name: Rascal-Bot
description: This little guy seems to like to hang out at the fringes of cataclysmic events. There is no evidence to suggest he has anything to do with the cause of these events, though - he's probably just an observer. Or maybe he just gets lost on his trek to other places.

name: Lil' Bling
description: This handsome little robot is the spitting image of his "Dad", Blingtron 4000. As a Blingtron's generosity circuits don't mature until they have been built to maximum specification, you shouldn't expect any free handouts from him.

name: Blackfuse Bombling
description: The first bombling created in the Underhold, Siegecrafter Blackfuse couldn't bear to see it destroyed, and kept it as a friendly, if explosive, pet.

name: Death Adder Hatchling
description: Late in life, if the environmental conditions are correct, a Death Adder may shed its skin and undergo a transformation into an Imperial Python.

name: Jademist Dancer
description: The Jademist Dancers of the Timeless Isle have a curious attraction to the steam vents of the northwestern shore.

name: Vengeful Porcupette
description: One of the beasts left on the Timeless Isle when it shifted through time, most likely sacrificed by the Ordon to their demigod, Ordos.

name: Macabre Marionette
description: These possessed puppets are given a semblance of life by whimsical spirits of the departed.

name: Murkalot
description: We're Crusaders from a fable. We dance whene'er we're able. We do routines and chorus scenes, with footwork impeccable!

name: Iron Starlette
description: This massive weapon of destruction has been miniaturized for use in the garden. Moles beware!

name: Weebomination
description: Made from bits and pieces of vanquished battle pets, dark magic, and just a pinch of love.

name: Crazy Carrot
description: Left to their own devices, carrots will simply lose their minds.

name: Elekk Plushie
ability5: Who's The Best Elekk In The Whole World?

name: Nightshade Sproutling
description: From seed to flower, a tiny terror is grown.

name: Molten Corgi
description: Loves to herd imps, roll around in lava, and snuggle with elemental lords.

name: Syd the Squid
description: This tiny squid seems to enjoy wearing pants, but where in the world would you find some that fit?

name: Blazing Cindercrawler
description: Tiny, incinerated corpses of various insects line its cage.

name: Widget the Departed
description: Not even death would stop this kitten's insatiable curiosity.

name: Frostwolf Ghostpup
description: The little wolf told to stay.rnWatching, waiting, for vacant prey.rnToo proud to leave, she slipped away.rnUnburdened now, forever free to play.

name: Ikky
description: Kaliri hatchlings feast on grubs when they're young, and eventually graduate to anything smaller than themselves.

name: Hatespark the Tiny
description: His hate is not diminished by size.

name: Firewing
description: Don't line her cage with paper unless you want a fire.

name: Bronze Whelpling
description: The Bronze Whelpling was lost in time until an unusual event allowed her to escape.

name: Sentinel's Companion
description: The companion of a night elf sentinel, rarely given out as a gift.

name: Soul of the Forge
description: When forging enchanted steel, bits of magic seep into the coals. Over a period of years, decades even, the unbound energy slowly takes form, creating a tiny elemental being of immense fortitude.

name: Golden Dawnfeather
description: It's said the feathers glitter like gold when the rising sun shines upon them.

name: Son of Sethe
description: Godlike being now in travel size.

name: Cerulean Moth
description: Delicate and dangerous, brilliant and bold, a beauty worth more than gold.

name: Sapphire Firefly
description: It has been referred to as "the flying gem" due to its similar luster to the finest of sapphires.

name: Bone Serpent
description: Young bone serpents will try to burrow into a living creature's skull and devour their brain. So you may want to wear a night cap.

name: Servant of Demidos
description: Demidos created a great many servants when he was hosting parties for other void lords.

name: Grommloc
description: No matter how much he screams, never give him demon blood.

name: Trunks
description: A magical friend created with equal parts adventure and spirit.

name: Fragment of Anger
description: It's just a little mad.

name: Sister of Temptation
description: She's the devil on your shoulder, whispering in your ear.

name: Graves
description: In one invasion of the Haunted Mines, a team of heroes only managed to collect a single skull. The golem that resulted, too small to do much damage to the enemy towers, wandered off into the Nexus, eventually finding its way to Azeroth.

name: Nibbles
description: This young stalker was easily swayed from Sargeras' grasp by a handful of Magical Mini-Treats.

name: Fledgling Kingfeather
description: While other species of birds take turns leading the flock during migration, the kingfeather always remains in the lead. Whether this is an effort to help the rest of the flock conserve energy or out of dominance remains unknown.

name: Fledgling Warden Owl
description: A young companion in need of training.

name: Stormborne Whelpling
description: Its scales are electrified, making it exceedingly tricky to cuddle.

name: Ghost Maggot
description: If a live maggot eats the dead, what does an undead maggot eat?

name: Rose Taipan
description: The last thing you'll see is a streak of red.

name: Broot
description: I am Broot.

name: Dust Bunny
description: This very elusive creature likes to hide in places where many adventurers don't frequently travel.

name: Knockoff Blingtron
description: Don't want to break the bank on that new robot? Have a little helper at half the cost! Come down to Goblin Experimental Engineering Korporation and put in your order! All sales final.

name: Baby Winston
description: An intelligent ape that claims he is from 'the moon'. Does he mean the White Lady, or the Blue Child?

name: Trigger
description: Ever wanted to cuddle with a gun? Introducing Trigger, the Cuter Shooter.

name: Coastal Sandpiper
description: It enjoys long walks on the beach.

name: Benax
description: Younger brother to Anax. Big brother to Cenax and Denax.

name: Rescued Fawn
description: With enough of your love, and tiny milk bottles, she will grow strong enough to rejoin the wild.

name: Legionnaire Murky
description: A proud supporter of the Horde, this tiny murloc left his clutch to seek out blue-clad foes to slay.

name: Boneshard
description: A small fragment of Lord Marrowgar, it will NOT stop assaulting your shins.

name: Blightbreath
description: The eternal answer to the question 'what's that smell?'

name: Stardust
description: In the end, we are all wrought from stardust.

name: Direbeak Hatchling
description: Direbeak falcosaurs are heartier than other falcosaur species, but cannot smell as well. They prefer pungent meals and will often eat carrion that has been sitting in the sun for days.

name: Bloodgazer Hatchling
description: Though they may look fierce, the bloodgazer species of falcosaur has a beak that makes it predisposed to consuming fruits.

name: Hearthy
description: Crafted by a great and powerful wizard who refused to wear robes with pockets.

name: Scraps
description: He's one cowardly companion, because he's got no guts...

name: Twilight
description: This energetic kitten changes colors depending on its mood.

name: Shadow
description: Lost on Argus and overtaken by darkness, this playful fox can shrug off the void just by being by your side.

name: Sneaky Marmot
description: This marmot has been with you this entire time. He's that good.

name: Mining Monkey
description: Best keep him away from any cannons.

name: Twilight Clutch-Sister
description: Even very small things can be corrupted, the apocalypse is for everyone.

name: Blazehound
description: Some say it's the pup of Riplimb and Rageface, others say 'I don't want to think about that.'

name: Infernal Pyreclaw
description: During his time in the Firelands, Fandral would often grow bored and work shaping magic on the local flora and fauna.

name: Faceless Mindlasher
description: Can't quite take over your mind, but capable of giving you a really bad migraine.

name: Amalgam of Destruction
description: Infused with the elementium ore used to plate the great dragon Deathwing, and one of the last remnants of the madness that nearly consumed Azeroth.

name: Fel-Afflicted Skyfin
description: Watch out when it spits.

name: Void Shardling
description: You have the odd feeling that it wants to kill you.

name: Pygmy Marsuul
description: It likes to be petted behind the fins.

name: Rebellious Imp
description: What are they rebelling against? The real question is what are they NOT rebelling against.

name: Mailemental
description: The Postmaster is often described as esoteric, mystical, even inexplicable. For the precious little known about the enigmatic mail-master, perhaps none outside of the wax seal can confirm the existence of the fantastical letter-loving Mailemental.

name: Guardian Cobra Hatchling
description: A newly hatched Cobra can be just as deadly as a fully grown one, if not more.

name: Baa'l
description: Not much is known about this otherworldly minion.

name: Shore Butterfly
description: Butterflies taste with their feet! I tried it once, but I only made a mess.

name: Spectral Raven
description: Suddenly there came a tapping...

name: Wicker Pup
description: She loves tummy rubs. Just watch out for splinters.

name: Ranishu Runt
description: Always hungry, and has a shockingly good personality.

name: Accursed Hexxer
description: No one knows where this haunted tiki mask came from, or why its so angry all the time. It seems to like you though!

name: Crimson Frog
description: This frog's peculiar red color appears to have evolved specifically for camouflage in blood. Spooky.

name: Bumbles
description: Bumbles may not have been the largest bee of the millions within the hive, but that doesn't mean he can't grow into a champion.

name: Kunchong Hatchling
description: Based on the size, the mantid appear to be re-growing their swarm, likely due to the presence of a new empress.

name: Coldlight Surfrunner
description: The coldlight once were quite common across the oceans, to the grumbles of many hunters, but no longer.

name: Giggling Flame
description: The most nefarious of the trickster spirits, and the reason why the pandaren invented fireproof pants.

name: Gearspring Hopper
description: Mechanical Toads can hop over seven million times before their gears begin to wear out.

name: Redridge Tarantula
description: The tarantulas that inhabit southern Redridge are smaller than their cousins elsewhere in Azeroth, but make up for their size with speed and ferocity.

name: Detective Ray
description: This is what happens when you try to one-up Pip Quickwit's tall tales of being stuck inside of dangerous creatures.

name: Tonguelasher
description: It has one solution to all of its problems: give em' a lashing.

name: Thunderscale Whelpling
description: These whelps are frequently captured by the denizens of Jorundall when still young and trainable.

name: Albatross Hatchling
description: The Albatross is capable of flying further than any other species of bird on all of Azeroth.

name: Happiness
description: This thing is equally as evil as it is adorable.

name: Lil' Nefarian
description: This pocket-sized Lord of Blackrock is too small to call out any classes, but he can still dish up a good insult.

name: Jingles
description: These dazzling hatchlings have a distinctive coat color that has been highly sought after by leatherworkers for generations.

name: Chitterspine Skitterling
description: The chitterspine make a distinctive clicking noise when they see prey in the open.

name: Blackchasm Crawler
description: In the lightless trenches and chasms of the Great Sea, life still exists.

name: Specimen 97
description: Specimen 97 escaped from his cage before being fully mechanized. Now, he seeks revenge.

name: H4ND-EE
description: When you need a hand, you know who to call.

name: Twilight Whelpling
description: A re-emergence of whelps outside of Grim Batol has the red dragonflight worried -- something is happening in the lost city.

name: Abyssal Slitherling
description: The eels that inhabit the trenches and chasms of Nazjatar are a favored food of many creatures that inhabit the area.

name: Kelpfin
description: Don't let the cuteness fool you, this little monster will jab your ankles the second you're not looking.

name: Pearlescent Glimmershell
description: When the sun shines on its shell just right, the light scatters in a thousand different directions.

name: Brilliant Glimmershell
description: A gift, found one day and saved for a meaningful occasion, should things ever turn around.

name: Drowned Hatchling
description: When the waves crashed down around the city, not all were fortunate enough to receive N'zoth's gift.

name: Utility Mechanoclaw
description: As handy as this invention is, it was also programmed to absolutely despise hand puns.

name: Arachnoid Skitterbot
description: No one knows who made these mechanical spiders, but everyone hates them.

name: Gruesome Belcher
description: The stench alone that this thing makes when it burps can easily ruin your day.

name: Slimy Darkhunter
description: Living so deep within the seas has made this species very sensitive to lights.

name: Gillvanas
description: Little is known about the true intentions of this murloc, but her followers are among the most devoted.

name: Finduin
description: An unlikely leader of murlocs that had to step into the role after the death of his father, Murgian.

name: Sunsoaked Flitter
description: The wings of this butterfly start off with no distinct color, but slowly change to yellow as they spend time in the sunlight.

name: Crimson Skipper
description: This butterfly is stained red from the blood of its enemies.

name: Eye of Corruption
description: This creepy eye is looking at everyone, always, and only has to blink once every 10,000 years.

name: Void-Scarred Hare
description: Only a being of immense power could scar such an adorable creature, unless this hare was already approaching the darkness...

name: K'uddly
description: His tentacles give you the best hug your brain has ever felt.

name: Corrupted Tentacle
description: Where did it come from, where does it go? Where did you come from, creepy tentacle?

name: Rotbreath
description: Dragonbreath Chili is nothing compared to the stench coming from the mouth of this thing.

name: Aqir Tunneler
description: These Aqir Scarabs are masters at tunneling through any terrain.

name: Oasis Void-Duster
description: Nobody is sure what sort of powder is coming off of these moths, and everyone is too terrified to find out what it actually is.

name: Void-Scarred Locust
description: Even some of the insects have succumbed to the void. They really do adapt and survive through everything.

name: Voidglower
description: Is the void glow in addition to their natural glow, or does it replace it? The world may never know.

name: Golden Chirper
description: The golden chirper has managed to stay its pristine self, despite corruption attempts from both the Sha and from the forces of N'Zoth.

name: Experiment 13
description: The name implies that there were 12 experiments done before this one that were less effective than sticking some guns onto a mechanical tiger. What could those have possibly been?

name: Animated Tome
description: Beware awakening the power of knowledge.

name: Starry Dreamfoal
description: When a full moon is visible, streaks of hair on the dreamfoal's mane start to shimmer and glow like shooting stars.

name: Fluttering Glimmerfly
description: For some reason, these blue glimmerflies are often afraid of water.

name: Helpful Glimmerfly
description: A glimmerfly can load up nearly fifty percent of its weight as pollen and still retain full agility while flying.

name: Micromancer
description: Even the smallest bones don't go to waste in Maldraxxus.

name: Foulwing Buzzer
description: The barbed mandibles on this species will dig deep into anything they bite, causing a lot of irritation.

name: Lost Quill
description: No longer lost, it's now considering a name change.

name: Shimmerbough Hoarder
description: These critters are capable of holding a tremendous amount of food in their cheeks for easy transportation between hiding spaces.

name: Severs
description: If a detached hand claps by itself inside of Torghast, can the Jailer hear it?

name: Spinebug
description: You got spinebugged!

name: Crawbat
description: For a pet that's all mouth, where does anything it eats go? Maldraxxus necromancers have dissected many of these pets, and have no answers.

name: Timeless Mechanical Dragonling
description: Dragons come in all types of temporal classification -- timeless, time-lost, and even infinite.

name: Silver Purrkin
description: Purrkins are a traditional pet of the Brokers and the two have a mutually beneficial relationship -- a necessity in Broker culture.

name: Lost Limb
description: Fragments of souls abound in the Maw, searching for meaning, or an end to their torment. But some just want to give you a hand.

name: Grip of Terror
description: These ensorcelled gauntlets are used by the mawsworn to capture escaping prisoners.

name: Chompy
description: One of several indistinguishable pets, all named Chompy.

name: Gilded Darknight
description: The golden armor on these mawsworn is flimsy and easily bent -- the gilded armor is a punishment.

name: Mord'al Eveningstar
description: A ruthless tormenter of the smallest souls. Some say he was known in life as "Thermaplugg."

name: Anxious Nibbler
description: You have never met a pet that is more about chewing.

name: Devourling
description: Devourers exist throughout the In-Between of various types and levels of power, but always seeking anima.

name: Archetype of Focus
description: One part focus, one part core, zero parts coherent or stable shape.

name: Resonant Echo
description: The core of a song that all but faded long ago.

name: Murkastrasza
description: Hatch-queen of the baby murlocs, Murkastrasza spent many years battling her bitter rival, Deathy.

name: Drakks
description: A drakonid hatchling is a curious sight, but now is the time for curious things.

name: Proto Avian Fledgling
description: While larger proto avians are known to feed on small animals, fledglings mostly eat insects and grubs.

name: Violent Poultrid
description: These poultrids are hostile, but never angry. They love every moment of every battle.

name: Gnomelia Gearheart
description: Spunky, funky, and just a little clunky -- she's a Gnomish engineer to a T!

name: Drazka'zet the Wrathful
description: Fooled aeons ago by the clever loa of death into a bargain of unceasing service, this tiny ancient being carries out his duties eternally red with rage.

name: Watcher of the Huntress
description: To its foes, this Watcher's innocent eyes belie the lethal danger of a prowling Huntress, waiting in the shadows.

name: Buttercup
description: His pink antlers make him the life of any party.

name: Violet Violence
description: Some very clever wizard or dragon or other magical being thought they were being clever when they decided to color an ice elemental purple for a very elaborate bit of wordplay. They were probably right.

name: Pricklefury Hare
description: This is the most pettable pointy creature you will ever meet.

name: Pistachio
description: Pistachio got her name in exactly the way you would expect.

name: Bronze Racing Enthusiast
description: This little racing enthusiast has never missed a race and has never met a racer she didn't like.

name: Snowlemental
description: When you feel a chill run down your spine, don't be afraid. It's probably just your pet snowlemental.

name: Gerald
description: Is it possible to rise from the ashes of time? Gerald thinks so and he will not be denied.

name: Palamanther
description: This salamanther wants to be your best friend.

name: Pilot
description: Still learning how to fly.

name: Primal Stormling
description: Raindrops whip around this creature with frightening speed, ripping and tearing anything that touches it. Experts say the best way to avoid injury is to give it a treat and some snuggles.

name: Roseate Hopper
description: Most brightly colored frogs are incredibly poisonous. The Roseate Hoppers are different because they are only credibly poisonous.

name: Black Skitterbug
description: After pestering the Dragonscale Basecamp for weeks, Granpap Whiskers discovered a way to catch them and use them to get rid of other more annoying insects.

name: Stormie
description: As an egg, this proto-drake was struck by a freak bolt of lightning. Years later, the lightning still lives inside.

name: Storm-Touched Stomper
description: This what your mother always warned you would happen if you ate grass that was struck by lightning.

name: Lady Feathersworth
description: Though she may be fashionably late, Lady Feathersworth will always show up for a party.

name: Endmite
description: This creature usually has a muddy appearance, but occasionally you may find one that shines a brilliant red.

name: Cobbleshell
description: Slimy, yet also gritty. It would not make a good meal.

name: Arfus
description: There must always be a Lick King.

name: Ambre
description: Nothing sparked joy in Ambre's heart until it found the perfect match.

name: Brul
description: Sure it's just a rock, but how much can it lift?

name: Aquapo
description: The fury of the sea in the packge of a puddle.

name: Teardrop Moth
description: Contrary to their name, these moths are actually quite happy.

name: Roggy
description: Roggy is the kind of snail that never gives up, no matter how hard things get.

name: Ysergle
description: Also known as the Dreamurk, Ysergle slumbered for many long years in the Emrgrled Dream.

name: Baa'lial
description: Also known as the Lord of Lies, Baa'lial is a master of deceit.

name: Iggy
description: Solid and dependable, Iggy is always ready for a fierce battle or a gentle metaphor.

name: Briarhorn Hatchling
description: Loves: Broccoli, playing, and smashing things. Hates: Meat, sleeping, and mean titan keepers who won't let you smash things.

name: Jeepers
description: This eye has witnessed untold horrors, and these fangs may be responsible for a few of their own.

name: N'Ruby
description: A lifetime of servitude to Anub'arak, then the Lich King, and now... you!

name: Fyrn
description: Fyrn will be the first one to show up at your birthday party and the last to leaf.

name: Lil' Frostwing
description: Feel the chill nipping at your toes! A menace of Azeroth, now in festive blue and travel-size!

name: Sergeant Quackers
description: When enemy combatants fly overhead, there's only one thing to do. Duck.

name: Aura
description: At a young age Aura donned her magic hat, took her crystal staff, and set off for adventure into the unknown.

name: Glamrok
description: Glamrok followed you back to the ship one day after a particularly good plunder, sensing your keen knack for treasure-finding.

name: Fathom
description: Weighed down by all the loot he has plundered. He could share the burden he carries but it turns out he's a little shellfish.

name: Bop
description: Woah there pardner. Were you really about to buzz by without saying howdy?

name: Aubergine Scootlefish
description: Not a squid, nor a kid, the scootlefish prefers to keep its ink to itself except under dire circumstances.

name: Hemospore
description: Fungal spores awash in the blood of fallen monstrosities.

name: Venomwing
description: It's not the most original anti-hero name. But it promises to be a compelling crossover.

name: Vibrant Glowfly
description: Though their light is sometimes mistaken for the glow of toxic substances or dark magic, nerubians and Arathi alike find these insects hauntingly beautiful.

name: Waxwick
description: In a miracle of dreams and wishes, Waxwick awoke and climbed off a kobold's head to pursue her own path.

name: Blightbud
description: Please keep your blightbud on a leash at all times! They are notorious for the havoc they can wreak on unprotected gardens.

name: Sir Shady Mrrgglton Junior
description: The shadowy creature has been following Sir Finley Mrrgglton around ever since he happened upon it during one of his expeditions. Having grown quite fond of the tenebrous friend, Sir Finley won't part with it easily.

name: Umbral Amalgam
description: These swarms of void energy cannot persist in Beledar's light.

name: Marrlok
description: Ancient Gorian blood runs through Marrlok's veins. As far as anyone knows, his desire to rest for long stretches of time on a sunny beach keeps his imperial ambitions in check.

name: Whoopy
description: Delivers the goods while also looking good.

name: Gale
description: A Stormrider's stormrook can not only navigate extreme winds with grace but can also conjure fierce tempests to defend themselves.

name: Lil' Flameo
description: Lil' Flameo is ready to drop foolish pets if they get in the way.

name: Thrillbot 9000
description: PRIMARY DIRECTIVE: ENGAGE IN HEROICS. PREFERED HEROICS: THRILLING. SECONDARY DIRECTIVE: BECOME HERO. PREFERED HERO: BIG.

name: Wavebreaker Mechasaur
description: And then, woosh! It comes stampeding out of the ocean and like, roars! Raaargh!

name: Viridian Mechasaur
description: It totally fell into a pit of acid but then it came back ten times stronger! So cool!!!

name: Fun-Size Flarendo
description: Nuh-uh! Yellow is coolest! It's themed after the original, who's totally gonna beat that stupid gorilla!

name: Gorillion
description: Gorillion possesses the strength of not one, but FIVE gorillas.

name: Mr. DELVER
description: Originally built by Dr. DELVER to compete with renowned treasure hunter Brann Bronzebeard. Never really panned out though, so now he just helps out.

name: Wily Rat
description: The thicker and more gangly the whiskers, the more devious the rodent. That's just basic biology.

name: Acid-Drenched Rat
description: Stop me if you've heard this one before: they fell into a vat of radioactive acid.

name: Cruncher
description: The itchy legs! The wiggly antennae! Okay, fine, he's not cute. But he's trying!

name: Venture Bombshell
description: In a pinch, Venture Co. workers might use these creatures for some impromptu demolition. Get it? Pinch?

name: Paleshell Crab
description: Paleshell cave crabs are said to be the tastiest variety. Perhaps that's why they're the hardest to find.

name: Varmint MK II
description: Before the Mark II, Varmints were a sorry excuse for an annoying and over-engineered pest. Now, though? They're absolutely infuriating!

name: Lime Roboclucker
description: The acid-green accents add a sporty vibe to this flightless robotic bird thing.

name: Reven
description: The game's afoot. Except when it is time to nap. Afterwards though, it's game on!

name: Grunch
description: It's best not to ask how Grunch acquired all these gifts because you know it's not because he's been nice.

name: Alchemical Runoff
description: Lab leaks are sometimes dangerous. Sometimes, they're cute. Sometimes, both!

name: Portentous Present
description: Previous owners of the crate have reported the disappearance of other pets from their collection.

name: Living Rose
description: When being adored, a Living Rose emits beautifully intoxicating aromas. When ignored, those aromas become actually toxic.

name: Snapdragon Pup
description: It is said that the bite of a snapdragon pup is many times stronger and more potent than the adults.

name: Storm-Infused Snapdragon
description: Snapdragon pups that were abandoned on the shores have become infused with the energies of the Seafury Tempest, as the other Siren Isle creatures have.

name: Craboom
description: Small, snappy, and with a temper as explosive as its name. Handle with caution!

name: Thrrrdgl
description: Thrrrdgl is content with not being a top choice or even a second choice. Thrrrdgl believes that first and second are the worst and third is the best.
